## 4.9 Tools Table
| Tool         | Purpose                                 |
|--------------|-----------------------------------------|
| Playwright   | UI automation and upload button validation |
| PyTest       | API and backend validation, DB checks   |
| JMeter       | Performance/SLA simulation              |
| OWASP ZAP    | Security and header byte validation     |
| tcconfig     | Network shaping for 4G simulation       |

# 5. Quality Objectives
- Verify upload button is only accessible to authenticated users
- Test rejection of upload attempts from unauthenticated or expired sessions
- Validate successful upload and processing of PNG/JPEG files up to 10MB
- Ensure files >=10.01MB are rejected with a clear validation alert
- Test backend detection and rejection of files with spoofed extensions
- Measure that the entire upload-to-render process completes within 2.5 seconds on 4G
- Confirm that uploaded images appear instantly on the public portfolio grid without manual refresh

# 6. Test Design Techniques
- Boundary Value Analysis (file size acceptance at 10.00MB, rejection at 10.01MB and above)
- Equivalence Partitioning (authentication states, file types)
- State Transition Testing (session state changes)
- Negative Testing (spoofed extensions, unsupported formats, multi-file attempts)
- Timing/Latency Simulation (network throttling to standard 4G for SLA validation)

# 7. Environments Needed
- Staging environment with user authentication and session management enabled
- API Gateway endpoint with logging and rejection hooks for invalid payloads
- Mock virus scanning microservice
- AWS S3 bucket instance with isolated test folder
- Network shaping/proxy tools for 4G simulation
- UI automation harness for real-time grid update verification

# 8. Resource & Timeline Estimate
- 1 QA Automation Engineer (2 weeks)
- 1 Performance Engineer (1 week)
- 1 Security Engineer (1 week)
- 1 Manual QA (1 week for exploratory/negative testing)
- Total estimated duration: 3 weeks (parallelized)

# 9. Risk Mitigation Table
| Risk ID | Description | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation Action | Owner |
|---------|-------------|--------|------------|-------------------|-------|
| R1      | Dynamic database connection drops during upload | High   | Medium     | Implement retry logic and alerting for DB failures | DevOps |
| R2      | SLA breach due to large file or network latency | High   | Medium     | Use JMeter and tcconfig to simulate and tune for 4G SLA | Perf Eng |
| R3      | Spoofed file extensions bypassing validation    | Medium | Low        | Enforce backend header byte checks and OWASP ZAP scans | Backend |
| R4      | Virus scanning microservice false negatives     | High   | Low        | Regularly update virus definitions, run negative tests | Security |
| R5      | AWS S3 write failures or permission issues      | Medium | Low        | Pre-validate S3 bucket access, monitor error logs      | DevOps |

# 10. Assumptions
- All test environments will be available and stable during execution
- Test data can be seeded and reset as needed
- Required tools (Playwright, PyTest, JMeter, OWASP ZAP, tcconfig) are licensed and accessible
- Upstream authentication and S3 integration are functional
